[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Class.forName functionality**\n\nI'm pondering how Native Image supports `Class.forName` for classes that are present. I wonder if it actually requires reflection metadata to function properly. This makes me think about whether it can really resolve classes at runtime if the class name is constant. It's intriguing to consider how reflection and runtime resolution interact in this context — I’ll have to look into it more closely to clarify my understanding!\n\n**Considering source class options**\n\nI’m thinking about whether the source class could be a library class, like `org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration`, but I wonder if that would work for registering annotations as components. It feels invalid since there might be no beans. For the binder configuration, I need to check if an existing library configuration creates a binder. I can look into `TestSupportBinder` to see if that works. Let’s explore this further!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0824ed2b3669e1fc016a0b6d66541c81a38128fdc41f0fadf9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqC210wzexsoIJyRxU5kydNlbAED7kmwpYuWy1SUt8Qj5zQF2N-_zWHvzrHDMjgpr0-49dnzP_2A2UfllBNExyKVDAlXHsdviEBE5-7cCYKHPYtYTN8SngNrtdrKGPclfQTzfBJCjaYPWGqOYCn6FPRidq-8kva9oR3KtQkOWxQZwj_C5nrza9geCi1Hx-jKv2i3CZ2QEtMNg_0jZWy_U1XOe4vY6dfi4umLE3U6ZQItqz1QRzqf6ILabrm38kfJDjWDMvEa9ik1NhbyS9sOGEw2XdSL4NaKOZ9vljTtwqBV5GtPQZXT5cwvKMcMD0V48En_3qRz42Lgvk2NHdeNorRgEy4xkGVTaeqsh4xhiqaO6ciN6mRjAa4efuCwcJlFSiGPz9zaf5V2TTPPmNBCCwad7igxUMY4jepYIVfXzCDtpVjszWU5XHMCtkKpRa-2KpoceuamzBxAfpd2pG-qrHk0K2b0SRCUryIP9-ShB2dF016z0B4b8I7AXH718lstkDRdJCbnuyOgzplcvd4e8yxnHkoCSjg4XgSEBePf7GOlgDITPJXPq0weJt_83FPw43k9UVouYVgY6d_xCt4SSVGGV_WAQu_fqnxyz9p8423x-j4HGsNmfSp0aAPwX7OFtjiNDZ9p3TEHUr5GvtAoMCNTSkNlO1ViAJ6S-nSLzaqudrCwjpuqCymiQK9_4fDhBAfqV7zoG3mRDxxrPhEebk5DOSr1ZQz60ttcVpAZ4Gh5SA0NUrEzoNDUhaswZZa1cdq30A-5IL_5QguEvm4Zf8A