 considering the potential violation of rules by dynamically class loading helper nested classes. Without direct reflection, the public API requires string sources, so maybe I could set the source to `DefaultBinderFactoryTest.class.getName()`, which is a top-level public test. However, that would make Spring process a JUnit test class as though it were configuration, which seems odd since there’s no @Configuration annotation. I wonder if it might still register a generic bean. It could get complicated. I should check if `spring.main.sources` allows multiple entries. Also, `DefaultBinderFactory` only calls getResources under certain conditions, which include ensuring our binder properties aren’t empty. I think I need to retrieve resources before refreshing the child context at the indicated line.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0824ed2b3669e1fc016a0b6d86c8c881a39ccb1b541d03e9cc\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqC22UGVLB-ECc4i0X4fNVczIl7mS1v857fnnmQQ2FlonP24-iCuDUxyT4034RIdXuDyFZybcIUN69nAJQbPbkECyHCtbeMOyzOBVolf-5VGYxKvdQ_le63EeRYdXY35o2RK8Y_mLDJux-0lnljGgAZ_kgbI9_Gk7spqHBJwwYC-uzKiQmmGmIyyCi2i0ufb7ZrWqxgND-KB81NqtbUWryuYVOrAqCma8o5FGBYxZMz2Yw3XXH9ebs0uFd6HVQ8EVP8U9JuDV7PRHeem0wPieWjn7H4fkeqtvlvgj9F2ipeQdDs7Hr4ie_-MuDzZGvblxc-NLd9G5FBK9UjgQALvusfJd0xdwCKSf9gw1obOL13rm-6JJ1iAhSgDaIwc5eiHfkKtLMYHPomIn0EbOCnYzlqHS-5gw1QHGD_J9AilE2H-Vnj3vsm0EPDV2b58sTVWCwqzq58q-f3H8UttKPfRC0OaX-_nFg8BI62z-lBIyRLImiByCJWa60qDCSs8n9evS_exxEWrdW7sKlhmisEIynriQZQCFwypVoZRcpRBPzRsKaS5X3fRiO3u05b_hLAK2_Gnd7yVaIBIprHeAYxh5-Hm7T3QMZfTAblJZ1Q7U3fMabJl-FEJwwZKG2fVU3HRKemz9hotx3VeYc-IFGMqFoMC2IJHL5d8gdEioklRzwT9AWcBn8PB6UIwThJNQRq0WdFQIUKcc8VqpFmrkn4NtAFrmVhVWTv5vFj8RDOUzjtRYZ3JvQw8BXjyInuRLXVNXYqOEA81I4EZHEDjq1JRKjSxJt8M4gyFdbEmzRrnDwWfe04hvX-27CysdGvY6sDP2oC3tJgUGjklzgNb2H7KYES4RU27P5cAh_D6c7bRo3BbxF40CR8MbydrBcP0ig91Q3rLvGxzIqXXzX8fGu1Lrlov1FM6j5GpwFqcg93EkL2CQJO46Wgv86nCKYaEnm_LmyzCNqa8Z2Pb0J3j9fTS48YQraUSf2dxHMH96E8tQNVkWptqFR5o1CsGcOZPDY_igK8kBjbuHGY3ELEfxsu4CU0ABY